text: so at mica this is the short summary of
pep talk or kabocha squash stir-fry with
Thai basil a healthy and easy dish great
for your weeknight dinner for the full
version the link is just right below
let's get started
heat a little oil in a wok or a saute
pan then add some chopped garlic once
the garlic starts to turn golden brown
add the squash and give it a quick toss
add some water soy sauce golden mountain
sauce and sugar let the squash cook stir
them every once in a while until the
squash is done but still firm add eggs
and scramble it just slightly to make
this recipe vegan you can also add
crumbled tofu instead of eggs once the
egg is mostly set toss everything
together stir in some Thai basil and
that's pretty much done serve with some
jasmine rice or as a side dish to
whatever you're having it's quick it's
easy and it's a great way to get kids to
eat vegetables for the full recipe with
all the details you can click right here
or in the link below if you enjoy the
